## 8. Traceability to the business rules

Every rule from `BUSINESS_RULES.md` that has a data-modeling consequence is addressed above. Rules with no data-modeling consequence (e.g. ACC-005's identical-error-message requirement, ACC-008/CAT-006's authorization checks, ORD-007's all-or-nothing checkout logic) are correctly **absent** from this document — they're enforced in application code against the schema above, not by the schema itself, and inventing a table/column for them would be modeling business logic as data it isn't.
